  "url": "https://www.ada.lk/breaking_news/\u0d86\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dd2\u0dad-\u0dbd\u0dd0\u0dba\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dda-\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd2\u0db1-\u0dc0\u0d9c\u0dcf-\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dc5\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca-\u0d91\u0dba\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca-\u0d89\u0dc0\u0dad\u0da7/11-396664",
  "time_ut": 1661665272,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d86\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dd2\u0dad \u0dbd\u0dd0\u0dba\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dda \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd2\u0db1 \u0dc0\u0d9c\u0dcf \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dc5\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca \u0d91\u0dba\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d89\u0dc0\u0dad\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Cultivated wastes on the protected list are excluded from it",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Even if the wild elephant causes crop damage, it is not removed from the list of protected animals, but the attention of the committee appointed for that is to remove other animals that cause crop damage from the list of protected animals.",
        "At present, 40 percent of the crops grown by Sri Lankan farmers are destroyed by animals every year. This situation has seriously affected the national food security.",
        "In the discussions with all the farmer organizations regarding the reduction of crop damage caused by wild animals, the farmer representatives stated that due to crop destruction caused by certain animals, they are unable to get proper income.",
        "A committee was appointed by the Minister of Agriculture, Wildlife and Forest Resources Conservation Mr. Mahinda Amaraweera to look into the matter. The committee includes the Secretary of the Ministry of Agriculture, the Secretary of the Ministry of Wildlife and Forest Resources, the Director General of Wildlife, and other officials.",
        "The animals that cause damage to the crops in abundance are the wild elephant, the peacock, the hippopotamus, the wild boar, the wild boar, the monkey and the wild elephant.",
        "However, the committee has decided not to remove the wild elephant from the list because it is considered a protected animal. Although the national animal is the Dadulena, the animal has been included in the list of endangered animals.",
        "Recently, a discussion was held at the Hambantota District Secretariat regarding the problem of wild elephants in Hambantota District, where Minister Mahinda Amaraweera mentioned that even if they are removed from the category of protected animals, an alternative work arrangement should be proposed by the sub-committee appointed for the same.",
        "Various measures have been taken for several decades to prevent the damage caused by wild animals to crops, but all of them have failed so far.",
        "The population of wild elephants in our country has exceeded 5000, but due to the increase in killings of wild elephants every year, if the wild elephants are removed from the list of protected animals, the killings of wild elephants may increase. Therefore, the wild elephant should be protected as a national resource. The minister also emphasized that the country gets a lot of income from wild elephants, especially through the tourism industry.",
        "However, the minister also mentioned that the relevant committee has a responsibility to prepare and propose a suitable and efficient work order acceptable to everyone in order to protect the plantations from wild animals.",
        "Many officials of the Ministry of Wildlife and Forest Resources Conservation participated in this event."
      ],
